items.text: Kangkong cuttlefish a must try!!!
Braved the queue (not me, hehe) @ Hill Street Char Kway Teow and was rewarded with silky smooth CKT that's really quite yummy. It's more to savory than sweet tho.
01-181: Hung Kang Fish Porridge and Braised Duck - great Teochew homestyle cooking!
Fishball noodles are the best! The balls are really soft and springy, and contain a lot of fish
Bedok south prawn noodle, the soup one - fail!
Try the duck rice. Gd
The char kway teow standard dropped.. dropped.. dropped!
Hill St. Fried kway teow, must try.
Spaghetti not al dente. No real bacon. Self service.
economical bee hoon @ Ban Seng Choon is a long-time favorite
Hock Seng Choon since late 70s till now still as good as ever. Duck rice is pretty good too. Kway chap pls avoid, overcharge and so-so only
fish soup always taste so good. ....
Come early for the hill street char kway teow! Sold out before 6pm on a Saturday!!!
Nasi Rawon is nice.
Warong jawa maintain nice foods!!!
Warong Jawa. Mee Rebus, Mee Siam, Mee Soto & Soto Ayam all $2. Nasi Lemak $2.20 with nice sambal. Must try. :)
01-235 Ji Shen Cooked Food: I don't think I can find any other place that sells cheaper economical bee hoon compared to here. Kway teow mee + luncheon meat + fried beancurd @ just $1.70.
Try Hock Seng Choon Fishball Kway Teow Mee, damn dope. Or you can opt for cheaper alternatives like Cai Tao Kway or Yong Tau Foo, under the price of $1.50.
The kway chap stall (there's only one I think) is very good. Piquant tangy chili and just the right amt of sweetness to the dark sauce. Can give the bedok central kway chap a run for its money.
Beli sarapan utk keluarga.
Wah Kee Cooked Food cuttlefish kangkong very nice ! Quite generous with mango strip..however price increase liao now cheapest $3,the sauce is also too sweet
Cha Kway Teow how to try? Long queue, no one take order properly, people cut queue, And food overrated ! Worst, the lady face long long rude too!
Ah Hua rojak damm power la tks to their signature sauce... Worth to queue for soo long for it.. Yummy ~thumbs up~
E fishball noddles is good but e queue quite long
Ah hua rojak best all time
Wong Porridge #01-245, fried rice with chic chop & egg is worth a try.
The duck rice is awesome , must try !
Hill street fried Kway Teow power... Koon Kee Char Siew and Duck rice also must try.
Best Youtiao ever!!!
Nothing special.. or i don't know. Same as other hawker.
Cheap teochew muay, $10 for 3pax
Try the Nasi Malaysia, very nice and delicious, can eat individually or in group at a resonable price...so SEDAP!!
成香 minced meat noodle soup is nice! Their noodle style is kind of unique cause they don't put the minced meat together with the noodle but in the soup. 3 deals you get: minced meat, soup and wanton!
It's near to the clinic I always visit when I'm sick. The pork porridge is a must have as it's cheap and yummy at $2.50
Hock seng choon fishball is very good but the noodles leave much to be desired.
Vegetarian options: tahu goreng, prata, Indian rojak, beancurd, vegetarian beehoon, bao, yong tau foo, yu tiao, putu mayam, thosai, lontong, rojak, kaya toast, pancake, fried carrot cake
Tong fong fatt chicken rice!
Chai tow kway: The style fr Original Changi Ten Mile Fried Carrot Cake #01-45 is slightly burnt. Playful crispy bits. Uncle has long history, serving CTK since 80s @ Somapah Village along Changi Rd
Ah hua rojak... More then 30 years liao still so good...
Tham Kee Cooked Food, simple, tasty fare that's often sold out by 1plus pm. Try the spicy sweet potato leaves, steamed fish.
Try the stall, Lao San Xiao Chi.
The mee soto here still power..
Hill str char kway teow is awesome if you don't mind the lard. Also, cheapest cigs outside of Changi Village here.
I like the Ah Wah Rojak, always order the you tiao, tau pok & cuttlefish to  go with the yummy sauce!
The Fried Kway Tiao is also very crowded during lunch time. Its very popular and tasty! Too bad I don't know how to appreciate.
Favourite fishball noodles (Hock Seng Choon), Ah Wah Rojak & Cheng Tng
Must try the award winning xin xi chwee kueh
Although lunch n dinner here is good , breakfast is lousy. Fresh fish @ the market is good; fresh n reasonably priced.
Hock seng choon fish ball kway teow mee
Bedok South Niu Ji Prawn Noodles.. Nicee
Nasi malaysia yummy2
01-48 still sells traditional beancurd. Choose non sugar for a healthier choice!
ATMs. POSB/DBS, UOB & OCBC cash-dispensing machines all round. POSB near main Bedok South Rd, the rest near 7-Eleven @ Blk 18
The hawker centre / wet market will be closed for a year for upgrading works.
One of the older hdb estates. Small shops, wet market and a small stadium nearby
Chee Cheong Fun from Bedok South market (opposite TJC) - tender n not stingy on sauce :)
Best prawns noodles here!
Must try their cheap and awesome Yong Tau Foo! :)
Nasi Rawon at Pondok Wak Nah is power!!!
Must try!! Stall 01-211 Hock Seng Choon Fish Ball Kway Teow Mee!!
Try Enak Nasi Ambeng! (#01-04)
try the prawn mee!
Bak chor mee: Con job fr Bedok Minced Meat Noodles #01-23. For $3, a bowl of noodles, 2 fried wantans, & a bowl of diluted minced meat + 1 meatball
Hill Street Char Kway Teow! Power!!!
The so-called blk85 bak chor mee stall's service is horrible, I got to repeat my orders 3 times, served the pple not in Q, and throw chilli in the ta pow plastic bag, 10 thumbs down!!!
Shi Jia Le has pretty good prawn mee.
Cheng tng v nice @ only $1.20
Hockey seng choon fish ball noodle not as good as 30 yrs back with stall helper f*** up attitude.. not worth coming to eat again.. I wouldn't come again..
Try hill street chao kuay teow.
Kway chap here damn tasty. Mmm.
Hill Street Char Kway Teow, Hock Seng Choon Fishball Noodles. The former once a month if you want to preserve your arteries and the latter, I recommend the Kway Teow in Soup.
Hill Street Fried Kway Teow & Hock Seng Choon Fish Ball Kway Teow Mee are the 2 most popular stalls here. Having tried both stalls personally, I feel they are very worth queueing for.
Fish ball noodle and the Hokkien mee. Fish head soup stall not bad too...
hill street char kway teow, fishball noodle, niu ji prawn noodle, fried rice chicken chop.
Awesome prawn noodles during the day - go before 1.30pm latest! The same stall sells Hokkien noodles at night. Good stuff too!
Hill street char kway teow, seng choon fishball noodle, cuttlefish beehoon, rojak, 85 bak chor mee all must try
Guan Heng wonton noodles, baby!
Hill street kway teow very nice.
Try the Penang char koey teow,surely u'll love it!!
Hill street fried kway teow.   Superb
Hock Seng Choon Fishball kway teow mee is superb.
Food at Pondok Wak Nah n Warong Jawa is a must try.
Warong Jawa-Best Nasi Lemak, Moli Food Stall-Best Thosai & vadai. Nasi Malaysia-Best Malay Nasi Padang
Breakfast!
Hock Seng Choon fish ball mee... All time best... For More then 30 years also...
Must eat: Fish Soup
Rong Hua Yuan Hainanese Chicken Rice! Die die must try!!
Brunch with wifey  at Pondok Wak Nah - Lemak cili padi, sambal goreng , bergedil, paru, achar, rendang,crispy kacang  bills , reasonably price & yummy:)
